  "prompt": "Why did the Greece financial crisis occur?",
  "response": "The Greek financial crisis, which began in late 2009, was caused by a combination of factors:\n\n1. Structural economic issues:\n- Chronic government overspending\n- High government budget deficits\n- Large public sector with generous benefits\n- Inefficient tax collection system\n- Widespread tax evasion\n\n2. Debt accumulation:\n- Greece borrowed extensively, accumulating massive public debt\n- Government spent more money than it collected in revenues\n- Borrowed at low interest rates after joining the Eurozone in 2001\n\n3. Global financial context:\n- 2008 global financial crisis exposed Greece's economic vulnerabilities\n- Reduced international lending and investment\n- Economic recession impacted government revenues\n\n4. Accounting irregularities:\n- Greek governments historically misreported economic statistics\n- Concealed true extent of budget deficits\n- Violated European Union fiscal rules\n\n5. Loss of economic competitiveness:\n- Uncompetitive economic structure\n- High labor costs\n- Limited industrial and export capacity\n\n6. Eurozone monetary policy:\n- Inability to devalue currency due to shared Euro\n- Limited monetary policy flexibility\n\nThese factors combined to create a severe debt crisis that required multiple international bailouts and extensive economic reforms.",
